  "body": "This is a follow-up to https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/74877\r\n\r\nPrior to https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/74877, Godeps/LICENSES included a copy of a dependency's LICENSE file for every package of the dependency we referenced.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/74877 switched to aggregating licenses at the module level. This is better in most ways, but means we don't have a fast way to check the licence for a particular vendored package (we have to manually drop the last path segment until we find the module root and the associated LICENSE file).\r\n\r\nSome options:\r\n* `vendor/modules.txt` lists the packages included from each module we depend on; we could munge that into the aggregated LICENSES file, so we have a package listing along with each included license\r\n* thoughts from @thockin: \"What I want to have is a directory tree of copies of licenses, with nmetadata about fingerprint (this pattern-matches as apache2) and per-pkg xrefs, so for any pkg I can trivially see what the license text is and what the category is, and diffs are useful\"\r\n\r\n/sig release\r\n/cc @cblecker \r\nfyi @thockin ",
